(fetchWidth, nL2TLBEntries).explanation: Fetch width determines how many instructions are fetched per cycle while L2 TLB entries are a fixed hardware resource for address translation, with no direct causal relationship between instruction fetch bandwidth and TLB capacity;

(fetchWidth, ICacheMiss).explanation: Higher fetch width increases the demand for instruction cache bandwidth and can lead to more cache misses when the cache cannot supply the required number of instructions per cycle;

(fetchWidth, numLdqEntries).explanation: Fetch width affects instruction throughput in the front-end while load queue entries are a back-end resource for memory operations, with no direct causal relationship between these pipeline stages;
